  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance for Vulnerable Older People in Ukraine</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will address several key issues identified by HelpAge International and others in Eastern Ukraine. As a result of the conflict and ensuing displacement and restrictions on movement, many older people have been left behind in dangerous or isolated situations, often without any form of external support from the Government or other humanitarian actors. Those who have mobility or sensory impairments are most vulnerable to extreme isolation. Few opportunities for social interaction exist, and many actors are not effectively meeting the needs of these individuals in their programmes. The project will tackle these issues through two main elements. The first part of the project will target vulnerable older people, including those with a disability. Vulnerable older people, particularly those who are homebound and suffer from isolation and lack of access to services and resources will be provided with home visits that will support them with basic tasks while building their own independence and seeking more sustainable sources of support. To address the wider issue of older people not having sufficient access to support, HelpAge will work with key actors in Ukraine to help them ensure their needs assessments, analysis and responses not only include older people, but effectively address their specific needs. An Age and Disability Technical Working Group will be established to ensure inclusion through data collection &amp; monitoring, technical advice and advocacy.</narrative>
  </description>
